{"id": "space-soyuz-p-158", "type": "fact", "statement": "Soyuz-P was a proposed Soviet combat spacecraft designed to intercept enemy satellites.", "explanation": "In the 1960s, the Soviet Union designed Soyuz-P as a crewed anti-satellite weapon. A cosmonaut would approach an enemy satellite, inspect it, and either disable or destroy it. The concept was eventually abandoned in favor of uncrewed interceptors.", "wowFactor": "The Soviets planned to send cosmonauts to physically grab and disable enemy spy satellites in orbit!", "quizQuestion": "What was the proposed purpose of Soyuz-P?", "correctAnswer": "To intercept and disable enemy satellites", "distractors": [{"text": "To carry tourists to space", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "To land on the Moon", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "To photograph Earth", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "To repair friendly satellites", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "To test weapons in orbit", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "To deploy nuclear warheads", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "To serve as an orbital laboratory", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "To dock with American spacecraft", "difficultyTier": "hard"}], "variants": [{"question": "Why was Soyuz-P eventually abandoned?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Uncrewed interceptors were preferred", "distractors": ["It was too expensive", "The Cold War ended", "It kept failing tests"]}, {"question": "Which Soyuz variant was designed as a space weapon?", "type": "reverse", "correctAnswer": "Soyuz-P", "distractors": ["Soyuz-T", "Soyuz-TM", "Soyuz 7K-T"]}, {"question": "Soyuz-P was actually built and flew in orbit.", "type": "true_false", "correctAnswer": "False", "distractors": ["True"]}], "difficulty": 4, "funScore": 9, "visualDescription": "A menacing-looking Soyuz spacecraft with grappling arms approaching a satellite in shadow. Cold War era styling with red star emblem, dramatic lighting from the sun.", "ageRating": "kid", "category": "s